                    <div class="writing-type">
                        <h3>Food Security and Technology</h3>
                        <hr>
                        <p>
                            <a href="./assets/writing_projects/academic/food security and technology.pdf" target="_blank">PDF</a>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            This is a paper that explores a current issue in science and technology that I wrote for WRIT 3152 Writing on Issues of Science and Technology. Specifically, it analyzes the public, scientific debate about food security and technology. In addition, it makes the argument for the transfer and access of biotechnology products for poor, malnourished people in Sub-Saharan Africa. The core of the food security debate in the 21st century is the issue of access to food and technological resources for agriculture. As you read through this paper, the important questions in this debate that you should think about are the following:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>
                                Who will have access to the biotechnology products like genetically modified organisms?
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                What are the benefits, challenges, and risks of globalization and increased availability of such technology?
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                        <br>
                    </div>
                    <div class="writing-type">
                        <h3>Visual Rhetorical Analysis</h3>
                        <hr>
                        <p>
                            <a href="./assets/writing_projects/academic/Visual Rhetorical Analysis.pdf" target="_blank">PDF</a>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            This is a visual rhetorical analysis of the <a href="http://www.bbc.com/news/" target="_blank">BBC news home page</a> that I wrote for WRIT 3671 Visual Rhetoric and Document Design.  This project includes an overview of the rhetorical situation (audience, purpose, and context) for the BBC news home page; an analysis of the intra-level, inter-level, and supra-level design elements on this page; and an analysis of the rhetorical strategies that this page uses, including arrangement, emphasis, clarity, ethos, and tone design strategies. At the end of the document, you will find screen shots of the BBC page with callout boxes that visually summarize the analysis.
                        </p>
                        <br>
