                    <div class="writing-type">
                        <h3>Design Analysis of Wii Remote</h3>
                        <hr>
                        <p>
                            <a href="./assets/writing_projects/academic/design analysis wii.pdf" target="_blank">PDF</a>
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        This is a design analysis of the Nintendo Wii Remote, which I wrote for WRIT 4501 Usability and Human Factors in Technical Communication.  For this project, I selected an “everyday thing” from my house that has interesting usability aspects. Given the Nintendo Wii Remote, I identified and applied the following design principles from Donald Norman’s <cite>Design of EveryDay Things</cite>:
                        </p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Conceptual model</li>
                            <li>Affordances</li>
                            <li>Constraints</li>
                            <li>Feedback</li>
                            <li>Mapping</li>
                        </ul>
                        <p>
                            In the conclusion of the paper, you will find an overall assessment of the Wii Remote’s everyday usability based on Donald Norman’s design principles and whether or not I find this object to be a good example of usability.
                        </p>
